00:11:04.393 --> 00:11:06.213
Better still is that you allow people

00:11:06.213 --> 00:11:09.323
to save their cart, and
you can get Shopify plugins

00:11:09.323 --> 00:11:10.863
that will allow you to do this

00:11:10.863 --> 00:11:12.883
where they can enter their email address

00:11:12.883 --> 00:11:14.363
to save it for later.

00:11:14.363 --> 00:11:17.453
This means that you can run
cart abandonment emails to them,

00:11:17.453 --> 00:11:19.573
it also means that if
they check in to your cart

00:11:19.573 --> 00:11:22.063
from another browser, you
can allow them to sign in

00:11:22.063 --> 00:11:24.033
and see the stuff that they've got there.

00:11:24.033 --> 00:11:25.453
But let's return to this idea

00:11:25.453 --> 00:11:27.963
of bumping them into an impulse purchase,

00:11:27.963 --> 00:11:29.973
'cause everyone loves a good
impulse purchase, right?

00:11:29.973 --> 00:11:32.153
Well, here I am on the Boots website.

00:11:32.153 --> 00:11:33.943
I'm just gonna add a product to my basket

00:11:33.943 --> 00:11:36.533
and then I'm gonna click
view basket and checkout.

00:11:36.533 --> 00:11:40.303
Now, I might be here on impulse perhaps.

00:11:40.303 --> 00:11:42.093
But what I'm seeing now

00:11:42.093 --> 00:11:45.003
is I'm seeing a little
nudge to get me to purchase

00:11:45.003 --> 00:11:47.053
because I've got a couple of free gifts

00:11:47.053 --> 00:11:49.483
already in my cart, so this is a great way

00:11:49.483 --> 00:11:51.973
of nudging people into
an impulse purchase.

00:11:51.973 --> 00:11:53.783
There's other stuff going on on this page

00:11:53.783 --> 00:11:55.543
which we're gonna come
back to in just a minute.

00:11:55.543 --> 00:11:57.743
Anything that you can do to push people

00:11:57.743 --> 00:12:00.453
into that impulse purchase
from just looking mode

00:12:00.453 --> 00:12:02.983
is a good thing in eCommerce conversion.

00:12:02.983 --> 00:12:04.633
Will make your Google Analytics

00:12:04.633 --> 00:12:07.173
eCommerce conversion rate very happy.

00:12:07.173 --> 00:12:09.183
Okay next, those unexpected costs.

00:12:09.183 --> 00:12:10.423
We've all been through it,

00:12:10.423 --> 00:12:11.683
you go through the process,

00:12:11.683 --> 00:12:13.143
you find the right products that you want,

00:12:13.143 --> 00:12:14.393
you stick them in your cart,

00:12:14.393 --> 00:12:17.313
you go to checkout, you see
a horrific delivery cost

00:12:17.313 --> 00:12:18.903
and you're immediately put off.

00:12:18.903 --> 00:12:20.223
Of course, the ultimate answer

00:12:20.223 --> 00:12:22.643
is to not have horrific delivery costs.

00:12:22.643 --> 00:12:24.693
Although weirdly, there are some occasions

00:12:24.693 --> 00:12:26.373
where you might want to
have high delivery costs,

00:12:26.373 --> 00:12:28.463
we'll come back to that
in a minute just as well.

00:12:28.463 --> 00:12:30.713
But the overall thing is
you don't want to have

00:12:30.713 --> 00:12:31.983
big delivery costs.

00:12:31.983 --> 00:12:33.833
Now there's of course an argument say,

00:12:33.833 --> 00:12:35.363
if you do have high delivery costs

00:12:35.363 --> 00:12:37.193
because what you're delivering costs

00:12:37.193 --> 00:12:39.033
a lot of money to deliver,

00:12:39.033 --> 00:12:40.143
where do you present that?

00:12:40.143 --> 00:12:42.533
Do you present that up
front on your website?

00:12:42.533 --> 00:12:44.273
For example, in a benefits bar

00:12:44.273 --> 00:12:46.983
knowing that some people are
just gonna bounce immediately

00:12:46.983 --> 00:12:48.853
as soon as they see that delivery cost.

00:12:48.853 --> 00:12:51.503
Or do you wait 'til they've
gone through the process

00:12:51.503 --> 00:12:53.343
of adding items to their cart

00:12:53.343 --> 00:12:55.823
to show them the delivery
costs at the end.

00:12:55.823 --> 00:12:58.833
Well Neil Patel says you want
to bounce them straight away.

00:12:58.833 --> 00:13:00.723
I completely disagree with that.

00:13:00.723 --> 00:13:03.393
I think you want them to
have gone through the process

00:13:03.393 --> 00:13:05.073
of adding stuff into their cart,

00:13:05.073 --> 00:13:06.693
they've put in that time and energy

00:13:06.693 --> 00:13:09.993
to find the right products,
they have a sunk cost already,

00:13:09.993 --> 00:13:11.883
then you hit them with the delivery cost

00:13:11.883 --> 00:13:13.273
if they're unattractive.

00:13:13.273 --> 00:13:15.313
Now of course, obviously
you don't want them

00:13:15.313 --> 00:13:17.353
to bounce at all if they
see your delivery costs,

00:13:17.353 --> 00:13:19.973
but if you're gonna have a
certain number of people bounce

00:13:19.973 --> 00:13:22.383
it's better to have that
as a high cart abandonment

00:13:22.383 --> 00:13:24.413
rather than a high bounce
rate in the first place.

00:13:24.413 --> 00:13:25.693
Now one thing you can do

00:13:25.693 --> 00:13:27.623
is advertise the trigger points

00:13:27.623 --> 00:13:29.123
at which people get free delivery.

00:13:29.123 --> 00:13:31.243
You can see here on
this B2B eCommerce site,

00:13:31.243 --> 00:13:35.403
free next delivery, orders
100 pounds and over.

00:13:35.403 --> 00:13:37.983
Great, so whatever the delivery costs are,

00:13:37.983 --> 00:13:40.733
I know that I will get free delivery

00:13:40.733 --> 00:13:41.873
over a certain amount.

00:13:41.873 --> 00:13:44.143
And it's at this point
where a high delivery cost

00:13:44.143 --> 00:13:45.983
potentially becomes an incentive.

00:13:45.983 --> 00:13:48.753
Let me explain, let's say
that I've spent 90 pounds

00:13:48.753 --> 00:13:51.873
on this site, and I know that
if I spend over 100 pounds,

00:13:51.873 --> 00:13:53.773
I get free next day delivery.

00:13:53.773 --> 00:13:55.683
Now it's at this point where actually

00:13:55.683 --> 00:13:57.693
weirdly, a high delivery cost

00:13:57.693 --> 00:14:00.303
can actually incentivize
a higher order value.

00:14:00.303 --> 00:14:02.623
Stick with me, let's say
that I'm on this site

00:14:02.623 --> 00:14:04.443
and I've spent 70 pounds.

00:14:04.443 --> 00:14:05.883
I go to the checkout

00:14:05.883 --> 00:14:09.043
and I see that my delivery
costs are 15 pounds.

00:14:09.043 --> 00:14:11.073
15 pounds, ouch.

00:14:11.073 --> 00:14:14.563
I also see that I get free
delivery over 100 pounds.

00:14:14.563 --> 00:14:17.643
Well I can spend another
30 pound on product

00:14:17.643 --> 00:14:19.023
to get free delivery.

00:14:19.023 --> 00:14:21.913
Basically another 15 pounds
to get 30 pounds worth

00:14:21.913 --> 00:14:25.613
of product, my additional
purchase is half price.

00:14:25.613 --> 00:14:26.733
Happy days.

00:14:26.733 --> 00:14:29.403
I'm now incentivized to
increase my average order value

00:14:29.403 --> 00:14:31.353
because that delivery cost was high.

00:14:31.353 --> 00:14:33.213
If that delivery cost wasn't as high,

00:14:33.213 --> 00:14:35.123
let's say it was only two or three pounds,

00:14:35.123 --> 00:14:37.223
I wouldn't have been as incentivized

00:14:37.223 --> 00:14:40.043
to get over that free delivery threshold.

00:14:40.043 --> 00:14:41.943
So you can see how a high delivery cost

00:14:41.943 --> 00:14:44.173
in some circumstances,
can actually increase

00:14:44.173 --> 00:14:45.538
your average order value.

00:14:45.538 --> 00:14:48.693
(squealing) You thought
digital marketing was simple.

00:14:48.693 --> 00:14:50.443
It's not simple, but it's definitely fun.

00:14:50.443 --> 00:14:51.973
Now going back to the boots example,

00:14:51.973 --> 00:14:54.953
you can see that they
show us how close we are

00:14:54.953 --> 00:14:58.503
to that free delivery threshold.

00:14:58.503 --> 00:15:00.583
I then have product here

00:15:00.583 --> 00:15:02.493
related to what I've got

00:15:02.493 --> 00:15:05.643
which I can use to nudge me over

00:15:05.643 --> 00:15:07.563
that free delivery threshold.

00:15:07.563 --> 00:15:08.753
Smart move.

00:15:08.753 --> 00:15:11.363
Now this isn't massively easy to implement

00:15:11.363 --> 00:15:12.900
and according to the
platform that you're on

00:15:12.900 --> 00:15:14.353
and the extensions you've got,

00:15:14.353 --> 00:15:15.943
you may or may not be able to do this.

00:15:15.943 --> 00:15:17.483
But it's a good thing to do.

00:15:17.483 --> 00:15:20.433
This is ideal because it
removes the thinking part

00:15:20.433 --> 00:15:22.453
out of your customer's checkout process,

00:15:22.453 --> 00:15:24.633
and anytime we can
remove the thinking part

00:15:24.633 --> 00:15:27.413
out of anything, we know
we're gonna get some results.

00:15:27.413 --> 00:15:29.883
Now here's a weird
example to watch out for.

00:15:29.883 --> 00:15:32.093
Here I am on boohoo.com

00:15:32.093 --> 00:15:34.433
and I'm being asked to put
in my shipping information

00:15:34.433 --> 00:15:36.373
before I can see any price,

00:15:36.373 --> 00:15:38.883
before I even see the delivery cost.

00:15:38.883 --> 00:15:41.753
On mobile, that's okay
because when I get down

00:15:41.753 --> 00:15:45.623
and see that my delivery cost
is a whopping five pound, 99

00:15:45.623 --> 00:15:48.083
on the five pound dress that I've ordered,

00:15:48.083 --> 00:15:49.813
on this example, you can't see

00:15:49.813 --> 00:15:52.383
but the product I'm
being is this halterneck

00:15:52.383 --> 00:15:54.253
puff sleeve, smock dress.

00:15:54.253 --> 00:15:55.833
You know, I just thought
I'd mix it up a bit

00:15:55.833 --> 00:15:57.433
for the Exposure Ninja videos.

00:15:57.433 --> 00:15:59.203
Anyway, it's a five pound product

00:15:59.203 --> 00:16:02.653
and they want to charge me
5.99 for next day delivery

00:16:02.653 --> 00:16:03.486
which by the way,

00:16:03.486 --> 00:16:05.823
isn't the cheapest
delivery option they have.

00:16:05.823 --> 00:16:09.253
They just want to charge me
for next day for some reason.

00:16:09.253 --> 00:16:11.243
Now this would be a real turn off to me

00:16:11.243 --> 00:16:13.523
but I can see that for a whole year,

00:16:13.523 --> 00:16:14.993
for an extra two pounds

00:16:14.993 --> 00:16:18.253
I can get free next
day delivery unlimited.

00:16:18.253 --> 00:16:20.863
Happy days, that sounds good to me.

00:16:20.863 --> 00:16:22.503
The problem is, on desktop,

00:16:22.503 --> 00:16:25.893
I don't get that same logical process.

00:16:25.893 --> 00:16:28.003
I go straight to the shipping page

00:16:28.003 --> 00:16:30.233
and I can see immediately
this delivery cost

00:16:30.233 --> 00:16:31.513
which looks really high.

00:16:31.513 --> 00:16:33.653
I've got no knowledge at this point

00:16:33.653 --> 00:16:35.303
that I can reduce that.

00:16:35.303 --> 00:16:37.773
I don't know that I can
change for different options

00:16:37.773 --> 00:16:40.173
and I don't know that the
premiere option is available.

00:16:40.173 --> 00:16:43.293
So I'd imagine that the basket
abandonment rate on desktop

00:16:43.293 --> 00:16:44.603
will be significantly higher

00:16:44.603 --> 00:16:46.153
because people are being hit

00:16:46.153 --> 00:16:48.293
with this high delivery cost immediately

00:16:48.293 --> 00:16:51.253
without any context or
information about how to lower it.

00:16:51.253 --> 00:16:53.593
Whereas on mobile, we get that information

00:16:53.593 --> 00:16:56.283
in a different order, which
makes it more digestible.

00:16:56.283 --> 00:16:59.043
The simplest way of course,
to get through all of this

00:16:59.043 --> 00:17:00.563
is to just offer free shipping

00:17:00.563 --> 00:17:02.643
but obviously it's not
possible for every business.

00:17:02.643 --> 00:17:06.073
Alrighty, the next thing
we need to get over

00:17:06.073 --> 00:17:08.883
is forcing people to create an account

00:17:08.883 --> 00:17:11.733
before they can even check out.

00:17:11.733 --> 00:17:14.273
Like we said earlier, we want
people to create an account.

00:17:14.273 --> 00:17:15.793
It's great if they create an account

00:17:15.793 --> 00:17:17.023
'cause then you've got their information,

00:17:17.023 --> 00:17:17.963
you can re-market to them,

00:17:17.963 --> 00:17:20.093
you can send abandoned cart,
all that type of stuff.

00:17:20.093 --> 00:17:23.073
Happy days, we love people
signing up for account.

00:17:23.073 --> 00:17:26.233
But what's not cool is
forcing them to do this

00:17:26.233 --> 00:17:27.813
before they go to the checkout.

00:17:27.813 --> 00:17:31.063
We just hate this for some
reason as human beings

00:17:31.063 --> 00:17:34.323
just like we hate being
burnt, we hate being killed,

00:17:34.323 --> 00:17:36.593
we hate being forced to sign up

00:17:36.593 --> 00:17:38.213
before we can checkout.

00:17:38.213 --> 00:17:40.483
I'm gonna show you some
bad ways of doing this,

00:17:40.483 --> 00:17:44.493
to prove that nobody gets it
100% right, 100% of the time,

00:17:44.493 --> 00:17:46.763
we're back to our old friends Boots.

00:17:46.763 --> 00:17:48.433
Well let's say that
we've seen these things,

00:17:48.433 --> 00:17:49.583
we like our free gifts,

00:17:49.583 --> 00:17:50.763
we're gonna be a just browsing

00:17:50.763 --> 00:17:53.673
that turns into an impulse
purchase, happy days.

00:17:53.673 --> 00:17:55.133
We click checkout.

00:17:55.133 --> 00:17:56.193
Then what happens?

00:17:56.193 --> 00:17:57.433
Well the first thing that happens

00:17:57.433 --> 00:17:58.913
is we go to this page.

00:17:58.913 --> 00:18:00.113
I want to checkout as guest,

00:18:00.113 --> 00:18:01.613
I don't have an account.

00:18:01.613 --> 00:18:02.973
Well the checkout as guest thing

00:18:02.973 --> 00:18:04.923
isn't massively obvious.

00:18:04.923 --> 00:18:08.263
The fact that this is a tab
isn't particularly clear.

00:18:08.263 --> 00:18:11.033
It's not highlighted,
it's not a clear button.

00:18:11.033 --> 00:18:13.333
But let's say I go to it anyway.

00:18:13.333 --> 00:18:15.393
I then have to click
through another message,

00:18:15.393 --> 00:18:16.933
they're forcing me to read stuff.

00:18:16.933 --> 00:18:18.743
I just want to freaking checkout

00:18:18.743 --> 00:18:19.973
and give you my money.

00:18:19.973 --> 00:18:22.183
Please stop getting in my way.

00:18:22.183 --> 00:18:24.603
But no, I have to click continue.

00:18:24.603 --> 00:18:27.913
Then what happens is totally inexcusable.

00:18:27.913 --> 00:18:30.663
I'm then forced to go through a reCAPTCHA.

00:18:30.663 --> 00:18:32.573
Are you freaking kidding me?

00:18:32.573 --> 00:18:34.813
Okay, fine, I'm not a robot.

00:18:34.813 --> 00:18:37.783
Then we have to wait for
all of this to happen.

00:18:37.783 --> 00:18:39.463
Absolute washout.

00:18:39.463 --> 00:18:41.123
You want people to be able to checkout

00:18:41.123 --> 00:18:43.083
as quickly as possible.

00:18:43.083 --> 00:18:44.583
By the way, if you think that's bad

00:18:44.583 --> 00:18:45.723
check this out.

00:18:45.723 --> 00:18:48.043
On zulily.com

00:18:48.043 --> 00:18:50.813
you can't even see products
without signing up.

00:18:50.813 --> 00:18:53.123
Am I qualified to sign up for this?

00:18:53.123 --> 00:18:54.963
Do I know anything about this business?

00:18:54.963 --> 00:18:56.713
Do I know that it sells
the right products for me?

00:18:56.713 --> 00:18:58.993
Do I know that they ship to my location?

00:18:58.993 --> 00:19:01.313
Do I know that the terms
are acceptable to me?

00:19:01.313 --> 00:19:03.683
Do I know that they sell
at the right price for me?

00:19:03.683 --> 00:19:05.293
No, I know nothing.

00:19:05.293 --> 00:19:06.823
I'm being forced to sign up

00:19:06.823 --> 00:19:09.233
before I can even look at the website.

00:19:09.233 --> 00:19:11.993
I just hope they're
not running PPC to this

00:19:11.993 --> 00:19:14.043
or any traffic to this.

00:19:14.043 --> 00:19:16.823
(shudders) All right, let's
look at a good example

00:19:16.823 --> 00:19:18.343
to cleanse ourselves.

00:19:18.343 --> 00:19:21.353
This is now Nike, or
Nike if you're American

00:19:21.353 --> 00:19:24.053
encourages you to become a member.

00:19:24.053 --> 00:19:25.653
And by the way, becoming a member

00:19:25.653 --> 00:19:27.203
is just their membership club

00:19:27.203 --> 00:19:28.813
so they have your signup details.

00:19:28.813 --> 00:19:31.853
So the first stage is we go
through the delivery details,

00:19:31.853 --> 00:19:33.143
we've put in our information

00:19:33.143 --> 00:19:35.403
about where we're sending
everything through to.

00:19:35.403 --> 00:19:37.893
We then have a choice of deliveries.

00:19:37.893 --> 00:19:40.093
We can either pay for delivery

00:19:40.093 --> 00:19:43.963
or free, we can become a Nike member

00:19:43.963 --> 00:19:46.523
and all we need to do is
fill in our information.

00:19:46.523 --> 00:19:48.633
Now to me, this is absolute genius

00:19:48.633 --> 00:19:51.113
because this is when membership
makes the most sense.

00:19:51.113 --> 00:19:53.313
They're not asking me to
become a member earlier

00:19:53.313 --> 00:19:56.023
than absolutely makes sense to for me.

00:19:56.023 --> 00:19:58.623
I'm essentially being paid four pound, 50

00:19:58.623 --> 00:19:59.903
to sign up for membership

00:19:59.903 --> 00:20:01.543
and that's what it feels like.

00:20:01.543 --> 00:20:03.283
So it's a great implementation

00:20:03.283 --> 00:20:06.933
and Nike, fair play for
delaying that request.

00:20:06.933 --> 00:20:08.613
Love ya, you just did it.

00:20:08.613 --> 00:20:11.273
Okay, let's address the credibility thing.

00:20:11.273 --> 00:20:13.033
The thing about people being afraid

00:20:13.033 --> 00:20:14.563
to put in their card details

00:20:14.563 --> 00:20:17.963
or are somehow unsure about the business.

00:20:17.963 --> 00:20:21.523
Now adding credibility
triggers to your checkout pages

00:20:21.523 --> 00:20:22.753
and your cart pages

00:20:22.753 --> 00:20:25.613
is not only a great way to
give your business credibility,

00:20:25.613 --> 00:20:26.813
but it's also a great way

00:20:26.813 --> 00:20:28.863
to answer any last minute objections

00:20:28.863 --> 00:20:31.943
people might have about things
like delivery reliability

00:20:31.943 --> 00:20:33.793
or the quality of your brand.

00:20:33.793 --> 00:20:35.203
Now one of my favourite spaces

00:20:35.203 --> 00:20:36.693
for analysing this type of thing

00:20:36.693 --> 00:20:41.683
is the at home orthodontics
solution industry.

00:20:41.683 --> 00:20:43.883
Right, Smile Direct Club and all of those.

00:20:43.883 --> 00:20:45.623
Now, this is a fascinating space,

00:20:45.623 --> 00:20:47.242
we're gonna do some videos on them.

00:20:47.242 --> 00:20:49.243
Loads of the businesses in this space

00:20:49.243 --> 00:20:50.923
just copy each other with
all of their websites

00:20:50.923 --> 00:20:52.663
basically look exactly the same.

00:20:52.663 --> 00:20:54.383
Now the customer journey for those

00:20:54.383 --> 00:20:55.603
who aren't familiar,

00:20:55.603 --> 00:20:58.062
you get an impression kit which you,

00:20:58.062 --> 00:21:00.143
there are little trays that
you stick in your mouth.

00:21:00.143 --> 00:21:01.703
You then send that back

00:21:01.703 --> 00:21:03.573
and then they start you on your programme

00:21:03.573 --> 00:21:05.083
of getting straight teeth.

00:21:05.083 --> 00:21:08.283
So this impression kit is
a really important sale

00:21:08.283 --> 00:21:09.723
because this is their tripwire.

00:21:09.723 --> 00:21:11.173
They're not really generating leads

00:21:11.173 --> 00:21:12.093
through an email capture,

00:21:12.093 --> 00:21:14.313
they just want you to
buy the impression kit.

00:21:14.313 --> 00:21:17.073
So this page becomes really important.

00:21:17.073 --> 00:21:19.403
The first thing to notice about this page

00:21:19.403 --> 00:21:21.913
is that it's both a product page

00:21:21.913 --> 00:21:23.543
and the checkout page.

00:21:23.543 --> 00:21:25.413
They don't have a separate page.

00:21:25.413 --> 00:21:26.833
This is obviously easier

00:21:26.833 --> 00:21:29.083
for a business that sells one product

00:21:29.083 --> 00:21:31.843
or one tripwire, so not
everyone can do this.

00:21:31.843 --> 00:21:33.283
But we can talk these lessons

00:21:33.283 --> 00:21:36.113
and apply them to the
checkout page as well.

00:21:36.113 --> 00:21:38.773
So notice how they've got
information about the product,

00:21:38.773 --> 00:21:40.913
just like we would expect
on any product page.

00:21:40.913 --> 00:21:43.533
We then go into the shipping stuff

00:21:43.533 --> 00:21:45.163
and the payment stuff.

00:21:45.163 --> 00:21:47.173
The bit that's really interesting for me

00:21:47.173 --> 00:21:49.443
is this credibility
that's added just below

00:21:49.443 --> 00:21:50.653
the shipping stuff.

00:21:50.653 --> 00:21:51.862
So if you're filling it out

00:21:51.862 --> 00:21:53.433
and you're like, eh, maybe not sure,

00:21:53.433 --> 00:21:54.823
maybe let's have a little look,

00:21:54.823 --> 00:21:57.793
more than one million
satisfied grinners and counting

00:21:57.793 --> 00:22:00.003
is a great credibility headline,

00:22:00.003 --> 00:22:01.373
absolutely love it.

00:22:01.373 --> 00:22:04.363
Then we've got people of
different ages, genders,

00:22:04.363 --> 00:22:07.083
races, you can see yourself in here.

00:22:07.083 --> 00:22:09.573
You can see that this
is a universal product,

00:22:09.573 --> 00:22:12.273
people are loving it, it's
user generated photos as well

00:22:12.273 --> 00:22:15.173
which gives credibility
which is fantastic.

00:22:15.173 --> 00:22:17.423
If we're still not
convinced, underneath that

00:22:17.423 --> 00:22:22.383
we have 21,000 five star
reviews on the site.

00:22:22.383 --> 00:22:24.523
So what's the impression
that you get from this?

00:22:24.523 --> 00:22:25.603
This is pretty safe.

00:22:25.603 --> 00:22:27.252
This is a safe bet.

00:22:27.252 --> 00:22:30.863
That uncertainty, that
doubt that you might have

00:22:30.863 --> 00:22:34.723
is washed away in a tide of testimonials.

00:22:34.723 --> 00:22:35.556
Love it.

00:22:35.556 --> 00:22:36.873
Now it's not possible for every business

00:22:36.873 --> 00:22:40.173
to add credibility stuff
like testimonials and reviews

00:22:40.173 --> 00:22:43.063
to their cart pages and
their checkout pages.

00:22:43.063 --> 00:22:44.433
For example, if you're on Shopify

00:22:44.433 --> 00:22:46.963
