00:23:40.773 --> 00:23:43.313
But allowing your customers
to pay with an alternate

00:23:43.313 --> 00:23:45.533
payment method, for example, PayPal,

00:23:45.533 --> 00:23:48.773
Amazon Pay, if their main
credit card gets blocked

00:23:48.773 --> 00:23:50.783
is a really good thing to do.

00:23:50.783 --> 00:23:54.173
Also worth noting is
the rise of Apple Pay.

00:23:54.173 --> 00:23:56.833
So if you've ever watched someone realise

00:23:56.833 --> 00:23:59.043
that they don't have their card on them

00:23:59.043 --> 00:24:01.043
and they have to go and type the details,

00:24:01.043 --> 00:24:02.983
